# Title: File Encryption/Decryption Via Gpg4win From Suspicious Locations
# Author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems), X__Junior (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2022-11-30
# Level: high
# Description: Detects usage of Gpg4win to encrypt/decrypt files located in potentially suspicious locations.
# MITRE Tactic: Execution
# Tags: attack.execution
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_gpg4win_susp_location.yml

CommandLine="*-passphrase*" Image IN ("*\\gpg.exe", "*\\gpg2.exe") OR Product="GNU Privacy Guard (GnuPG)" OR Description="GnuPG’s OpenPGP tool" CommandLine IN ("*:\\PerfLogs\\*", "*:\\Temp\\*", "*:\\Users\\Public\\*", "*:\\Windows\\Temp\\*", "*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\*", "*\\AppData\\Roaming\\*")